6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup><sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page: 121">:=E2=
=80=8A121=E2=80=8A</span></sup> Similarly, the components of random vectors=
 whose <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Covariance_matrix" title=3D=
"Covariance matrix">covariance matrix</a> is zero in every entry outside th=
e main diagonal are also called uncorrelated.
