template removal">Learn how and when to remove this message</a></small>)</i=
></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>The covariance matrix is important in estimating the initial conditions =
required for running weather forecast models, a procedure known as <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_assimilation" title=3D"Data assimila=
tion">data assimilation</a>. The "forecast error covariance matrix" is typi=
cally constructed between perturbations around a mean state (either a clima=
tological or ensemble mean). The "observation error covariance matrix" is c=
onstructed to represent the magnitude of combined observational errors (on =
the diagonal) and the correlated errors between measurements (off the diago=
nal). This is an example of its widespread application to <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kalman_filtering" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ka=
lman filtering">Kalman filtering</a> and more general <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_estimation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"State =
estimation">state estimation</a> for time-varying systems.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"In_micrometeorology">In mic=
rometeorology</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsect=
ion-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=
=3DCovariance&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D22" title=3D"Edit section: In=
 micrometeorology"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eddy_covariance" title=3D"E=
ddy covariance">eddy covariance</a> technique is a key atmospherics measure=
ment technique where the covariance between instantaneous deviation in vert=
ical wind speed from the mean value and instantaneous deviation in gas conc=
entration is the basis for calculating the vertical turbulent fluxes.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"In_signal_processing">In si=
gnal processing</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DCovariance&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D23" title=3D"Edit section: I=
n signal processing"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bra=
cket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The covariance matrix is used to capture the spectral variability of a s=
ignal.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Covariance#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>17<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
