Analysis" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Principal Component Analysis">Prin=
cipal Component Analysis</a></div>
<p>The covariance matrix is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Principal_component_analysis" title=3D"Principal component analysis">prin=
cipal component analysis</a> to reduce feature dimensionality in <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_preprocessing" title=3D"Data preprocess=
ing">data preprocessing</a>. The principal components are the dimensions th=
at explain the most variance in the data. A well known application is to in=
telligence, producing the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G_factor=
_(psychometrics)" title=3D"G factor (psychometrics)">g factor</a>. Another =
is to personality, with models like the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Big_Five_personality_traits" title=3D"Big Five personality traits">fi=
ve factor model</a> being derived from principal component analysis.
</p>
